  "text": "However, if temporal autocorrelations are present in the time series (i.e., in the case of nonsphericity), such that V is not equal to the identity matrix, the denominator of Equation 2 will no longer be the square-root of a v 2 distribution. In this case, Equation 2 no longer follows a t-distribution, which prohibits inference based on comparing it to a Student t null distribution [CITATION_1] .",
